description: 1799, borrowed from Swedish rotabagge, a dialectal word from Västergötland, from rot (“root”) +‎ bagge (“lump, bunch”).

entries.meaning: (now Canada, US) The swede, or Swedish turnip; the European plant Brassica napus var. napobrassica
(now Canada, US) The edible root of this plant
examples: Sometimes your royal dogs tear down our thatch,And then we seek the shelter of a ditch;Hog-wash or grains, or ruta-baga, noneHas yet been ours since your reign begun.
